of specificity of the effector, which runs against the desire of modern biology to reduce all cellular phenomena to a network of signaling and metabolic chains. In addition to that, there has been a dearth of studies of MC in situ; almost all that is known about MC has been obtained in test tubes using artificial macromolecules to mimic intracellular crowding. We have been trying to argue throughout this paper that regulation of CV by protein density is a viable hypothesis, and there are ways to study it in living cells, even if by the elimination of competing hypotheses.
